		<p>How anyone can find these photos &#8216;neat&#8217; or &#8216;cool&#8217; is beyond my comprehension. When I view these photos of desolation I feel an overwhelming sense of grief and loss for those who lost everything; home, family, even their lives. Thousands have died and more will die. The city is dead because most of the people are gone, and should never return. It should be left as a reminder of how wrong we can be when power (of any kind) is more important than people. Thank you for sharing these horrible photos.</p>

