			December 26, 2007 at 9:39 am</a>		</div>

		<p>Great pics! But there are huge mistakes in the explanations.</p>
<p>First of all the pics are about Pripjaty, which is nearer to the power plant, than Chernobyl itself. Pripjaty wasn&#8217;t a city, it had about 60 000 residents.</p>
<p>The Power Plant is NOT IN THE MIDDLE of the town, it&#8217;s about 5 kms from it. (see it on Google Earth if you don&#8217;t believe me)</p>
<p>There isn&#8217;t any kind of mutation in trees growing inside buildings, that&#8217;s just nature taking back the city.</p>
<p>I&#8217;ve been to the Chernobyl area this may. Here are the pics I&#8217;ve made:</p>
<p><a href="http://picasaweb.google.com/faluvegi/Csernobil_0705" rel="nofollow">http://picasaweb.google.com/faluvegi/Csernobil_0705</a></p>
<p>(text is in Hungarian)</p>

