		<p>I&#8217;m 31 years old. I&#8217;m Italian. When Chernobyl exploded I was 9 years old. I remember all of what happened and the feeling of a colossal catastrophe happened. The feeling of spread fear in our hearts. The feeling of defeat of human being. The uncertainty about the future. The woe for all Chernobyl&#8217;s victims.<br />
Chernobyl is a name that still today arouses dark shadows in my mind. Chernobyl is the defeat of man. It was one of history&#8217;s big mistakes. These photos are unique. They evoke tears to the eyes. Hope that memory is preserved and future generations don&#8217;t forget.</p>

