		<p>[...] Prypiat is an abandoned city in the Zone of Alienation, Ukraine. You&#8217;ll probably know of it because of the Chernobyl disaster. I realise it isn&#8217;t the cheeriest destination, but I find the idea of wandering around an abandoned city quite fascinating. Especially when you consider that everything had been left behind. We had planned to visit when we were in Ukraine last October, but unfortunately there weren&#8217;t any tours running that week. However, we did visit the Chernobyl Museum in Kyiv (safer, no radiation) and that made me want to go even more. There are more pictures here on English Russia. [...]</p>

